summary: The creator discusses three ETFs (Exchange Traded Funds) that helped them reach six figures by age 25 and that they plan to continue buying through 2026. The first ETF mentioned is VFV, which tracks the S&P 500 and returns approximately 10% annually. The second ETF is QQQM, which tracks the Nasdaq 100 and includes the top 100 tech companies, noting it is more volatile with higher highs and lower lows. The third ETF is VEQT, which is globally diversified and invests in companies worldwide. The creator encourages viewers to follow for more investing tips.
transcript: 3 ETFs that took me to 6-figures by 25. I'm continuing to buy into 2026. The first ETF is VFV. VFV is an ETF that tracks the S&P 500, which is the 500 biggest companies in the United States. So when you buy this ETF, you buy a little piece of all of those companies. On average, this ETF returned about 10% per year. The second ETF that I'm gonna be buying is QQQM. This ETF tracks the Nasdaq 100, which is the top 100 companies in the tech sector. This ETF is a bit more volatile, so higher highs and lower lows. And the last ETF that I'm gonna be buying into 2026 is VEQT. This ETF is globally diversified, meaning that it invests in companies over all over the world, not just in the USA. Those are the three ETFs I'm gonna be continuing buying into 2026. Make sure to drop a follow if you wanna get better with investing.
